docs.lead_paragraph: Well, here I am, safe and sound, in this renowned ",Prairie Port," ready to hold your readers by the button-hole as long as they may be willing to listen. No rail-car whisked and whirled me along until all sense was lost, save that of motion, and then pitched me into the big hall of the Planters' House, without an idea left to communicate to others.

docs.lead_paragraph: Alderman WAKEMAN in the Chair. CATTLE DRIVING THROUGH THE STREETS. Alderman MOTT inquired if the Committee on Ordinances were prepared to report upon an ordinance referred to them some two months since, to prevent the driving of cattle through the streets ? Alderman LORD replied that the ordinance prepared by the gentleman from the Twenty-first and Submitted to the Committee was under consideration.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE CHOLERA.--No new cases of cholera were reported at the Health Office yesterday. Dr. CLARK was a called to attend a young man--a resident of this city--who was attacked on Monday night, at Quincy, and brought hither in a chaise. The unfortunate patient was in a state of collapse, and there was but little hope of recovery. He was taken to Deer Island.
